Program: Outlook
Title: 20/07/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00j8sqr
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 21 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Josephine, the 70 year old widow who fled last year's post election violence in Ivory Coast. Josephine is one of an estimated 150,000 refugees who are still living across the border in Liberia. More than six months later she is still too scared to go home. Also, Colin Freeman, the British journalist held hostage by pirates in Somalia. And, the internationally acclaimed Romanian artist who creates collages from the rubbish dump where he used to live. Show less